[ctns_make id='gen_abs_prop_lt_c']

  [ctns_front style='font-size:150%;']
$$|x| \lt c$$
  [/ctns_front]  

  [ctns_back style='font-size:100%;']
$||x| \lt c|$ is equivalent to $|-c \lt x \lt c|$
  [/ctns_back]  

  [ctns_frontspeak]
The absolute value of x -- less than -- a constant -- c.
  [/ctns_frontspeak]  

  [ctns_backspeak]
When the absolute value of x -- is less than -- a constant -- c,  then the value of x -- is greater than negative see -- but less than positive see.
  [/ctns_backspeak]  

[/ctns_make]
